      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 2 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Red, White & Boom."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "March 5, 1770. Five colonists are dead. Eight British soldiers are in custody. And John Adams — future President, committed patriot — has agreed to defend them. You are his co-counsel. Five witnesses take the stand: Nathan Maverick (the victim's grief-stricken brother), Captain Preston (military, formal), Richard Palmes (moderate merchant bystander), Dr. Benjamin Church (hostile Patriot physician), and Private Montgomery (the frightened young soldier who fired first). Cross-examine each one. Then watch 12 historically-named colonial jurors deliberate in real time."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Sons of Liberty by another Week 2 entrant"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " where that demo puts you in the streets throwing snowballs, this one puts you in the courtroom defending the soldiers who fired back — same night, opposite side of the moral equation"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Three Claude endpoints run the trial. The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "testify endpoint"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " streams each witness's testimony via SSE — each of the five witnesses has a distinct system prompt personality, and the defense strategy you chose at the start (Self-Defense, Mistaken Command, or Lawful Military Duty) is injected so testimony responds to your legal angle."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "crossexamine endpoint"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " uses the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "evaluate_crossexamination tool"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to score your question: credibility_shift (−30 to +20), key_point_landed, opportunity_missed, and a witness_reaction in character. Your cross-examination skill directly changes each witness's credibility meter."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "jury endpoint"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " receives your defense strategy and all five credibility scores. Claude generates 12 named colonial-era jurors — merchants, coopers, shipwrights, clergy — each with an occupation, a vote, and their reasoning. The verdict scales with how well you cross-examined."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Choose your defense strategy — it shapes every witness's testimony and the jury's frame"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Read the streaming testimony, then type your cross-examination question"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Your question quality shifts the witness's credibility meter — weak questions backfire"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "After all 5 witnesses, watch the 12 jurors reveal their votes one by one"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
